{
  "doc_id": "491",
  "text": "As a promising thermoplastic material, PEEK possesses good processability, stable chemical properties, and favorable biocompatibility with an elastic modulus that is close to that of human cortical bone [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, PEEK is hydrophobic and bio-inert, which has limited its broad application [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Composites that possess tailored biological and mechanical properties can be produced by combining polymers and bioactive inorganic phases [CITATION_5] . In this study, HA particles were incorporated into the PEEK matrix via a compounding and injection-molding process, and the bioactivity of the prepared HA/PEEK composite was evaluated by in vitro and in vivo studies.",
